.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP 
Read the global config file
.PP 
This is the primary way to initialise radcli. Loads the configuration file, initialises the transport (including TLS/DTLS handshake when applicable), and returns an opaque handle for use in subsequent calls. The format is compatible with radiusclient-ng and freeradius-client.
.PP 
Standard RFC 2865/2866/2869 attributes are built into the library; the dictionary option is only needed for vendor-specific attributes.
.PP 
Recognised configuration options:
.PP 
acctserver: accounting server; same format as authserver.
.PP 
namespace: Linux network namespace name to use for socket operations.
.PP 
tls-verify-hostname: set to false to skip server hostname verification (not recommended).
.PP 
require-message-authenticator: set to no to accept responses that lack the Message-Authenticator attribute. Enabled by default per draft-ietf-radext-deprecating-radius (CVE-2024-3596 / BLAST RADIUS); only disable for legacy servers that predate RFC 3579.
.PP 
clientdebug: debug verbosity level (integer; 0 = off).
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
.B filename
path to the configuration file. 

.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
new rc_handle on success, NULL on failure. 
